ort. Given we recover phosphine, we suggest possible solutions (requiring\nsubstantial further testing): a small collisional broadening coefficient could\ngive narrow lines from lower altitude, or a high eddy diffusion coefficient\ncould allow molecules to survive longer at higher altitudes. Alternatively, PH3\ncould be actively produced by an unknown mechanism in the mesosphere, but this\nwould need to be in addition to cloud-level PH3 detected retrospectively by\nPioneer-Venus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Apr 2021 13:22:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-21"}
